text.tspan:
Based on the expert estimates and index by the
Economist Intelligence Unit (2006-2023)
. It combines information
on the extent to which citizens can choose their political leaders in free and fair elections, enjoy civil liberties,
prefer democracy over other political systems, can and do participate in politics, and have a functioning
government that acts on their behalf. It ranges from 0 to 10 (most democratic).
